1
00:00:09,500 --> 00:00:11,125
[rain beating]

2
00:00:15,250 --> 00:00:17,208
[thundering]

3
00:00:21,958 --> 00:00:23,958
[MARLYA crying]

4
00:00:25,458 --> 00:00:28,208
♪

5
00:00:29,916 --> 00:00:32,000
[door opens]

6
00:00:34,791 --> 00:00:35,916
Director.

7
00:00:46,708 --> 00:00:48,375
[MARLYA crying]

8
00:00:56,708 --> 00:00:58,666
[NEIN]
Beevee Liscar.

9
00:00:58,750 --> 00:01:01,041
How much blood
will it take to satisfy you?

10
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:06,666
I should’ve been there for him,
but I wasn’t.

11
00:01:06,750 --> 00:01:09,333
I failed.
And now he's dead.

12
00:01:09,416 --> 00:01:10,583
You're wrong.

13
00:01:11,916 --> 00:01:15,791
It’s my fault.
No one else’s. I’m to blame.

14
00:01:17,125 --> 00:01:21,875
-Is it anyone’s fault, really?
-Some things can’t be undone,

15
00:01:21,958 --> 00:01:24,583
whether it’s people
we weren’t able to save

16
00:01:24,666 --> 00:01:26,375
or mistakes we’ve made.

17
00:01:26,458 --> 00:01:28,291
[NEIN]
That’s an understatement.

18
00:01:28,375 --> 00:01:33,291
Fratanil’s gone! A Fairy Weapon.
Stolen while under our guard!

19
00:01:33,375 --> 00:01:37,583
Dorothea’s never experienced
a failure on this level before!

20
00:01:37,666 --> 00:01:39,416
[MARLYA cries]

21
00:01:43,791 --> 00:01:45,916
[NEIN] Regardless, we have
to move forward.

22
00:01:47,291 --> 00:01:49,875
We fight,
even if we’re down in the mud.

23
00:01:49,958 --> 00:01:51,708
Even bleeding we never stop.

24
00:01:51,791 --> 00:01:54,541
Instead we should
count ourselves lucky

25
00:01:54,625 --> 00:01:56,708
we still have
blood left to spill.

26
00:01:56,791 --> 00:01:59,708
We complete the mission,
no matter the cost!

27
00:02:09,791 --> 00:02:12,375
[GRIFF] Per standard protocol,
the Ministry of Fairies

28
00:02:12,458 --> 00:02:14,333
will assume custody
over the body now.

29
00:02:16,833 --> 00:02:18,208
How come?

30
00:02:18,291 --> 00:02:21,125
[FREE] We have fairy organs
implanted inside us.

31
00:02:22,458 --> 00:02:24,000
Did you forget?

32
00:02:24,083 --> 00:02:26,333
Strictly speaking,
they’re illegal.

33
00:02:27,666 --> 00:02:28,791
[FREE sighs]

34
00:02:28,875 --> 00:02:30,583
You shouldn’t be surprised.

35
00:02:30,666 --> 00:02:32,708
We already went over all this.

36
00:02:32,791 --> 00:02:34,708
Yeah? Maybe we did.

37
00:02:37,166 --> 00:02:38,791
[MARLYA]
Maybe I wasn’t paying attention

38
00:02:38,875 --> 00:02:40,250
even though it was important.

39
00:02:42,458 --> 00:02:45,375
Because I never imagined
this would happen.

40
00:02:45,458 --> 00:02:47,125
Not to someone in Dorothea.

41
00:02:50,125 --> 00:02:52,166
[whistle blowing]

42
00:02:57,416 --> 00:02:59,416
Farewell, Ozz.

43
00:03:13,500 --> 00:03:17,625
He died because of me.

44
00:03:17,708 --> 00:03:21,583
After all, I am a cursed child.

45
00:03:22,625 --> 00:03:24,625
♪

46
00:03:39,666 --> 00:03:41,750
-Hmm?
-[GONZALEZ grunts]

47
00:03:47,541 --> 00:03:48,916
[GONZALEZ sighs]

48
00:03:53,416 --> 00:03:54,958
-[knocking]
-[CHIMA squeaks]

49
00:03:57,291 --> 00:03:58,916
[knocking]

50
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:03,750
-[MARLYA] Yes?
-[KLARA] It’s Klara. Let’s talk.

51
00:04:03,833 --> 00:04:07,583
-Can I come in? Please?
-[MARLYA] It’s open.

52
00:04:16,250 --> 00:04:17,916
[CHIMA squeaks]

53
00:04:23,708 --> 00:04:25,166
[KLARA]
Listen to me.

54
00:04:25,250 --> 00:04:27,708
Don’t blame yourself
for what happened.

55
00:04:27,791 --> 00:04:31,291
What we do, no one said
it would be easy.

56
00:04:31,375 --> 00:04:34,541
Our job is to safeguard
unification and maintain peace.

57
00:04:35,625 --> 00:04:39,000
It’s hard, but that’s why
we must be so determined.

58
00:04:40,250 --> 00:04:42,416
-[MARLYA] I know, but...
-But?

59
00:04:42,500 --> 00:04:44,041
[MARLYA]
You’re wrong about this.

60
00:04:46,166 --> 00:04:49,625
[MARLYA] Everyone who’s close
to me ends up dead.

61
00:04:50,916 --> 00:04:54,375
-All because of me.
-Marlya.

62
00:04:55,541 --> 00:04:57,541
♪

63
00:05:02,375 --> 00:05:05,083
[MARCO]
Hmm. That’s the secret.

64
00:05:05,166 --> 00:05:09,458
The key is fairy-possessed fairy
organs and fairy organ fusion.

65
00:05:09,541 --> 00:05:14,333
Part of the mystery is revealed.
If only we had the Black Six.

66
00:05:16,375 --> 00:05:18,583
-[GRIFF] Minister.
-Ah.

67
00:05:18,666 --> 00:05:21,583
As you know, I still haven’t
been officially appointed.

68
00:05:21,666 --> 00:05:26,125
At times like this, we must
continue to observe protocol.

69
00:05:26,208 --> 00:05:27,916
Of course, Vice Minister.

70
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:31,125
As for the retrieval,
I assume it’s been completed.

71
00:05:31,208 --> 00:05:33,500
Yes, and with no delay.

72
00:05:33,583 --> 00:05:35,583
What are your thoughts
on the Black Four?

73
00:05:35,666 --> 00:05:38,625
It’s truly astonishing.
One thing’s certain.

74
00:05:38,708 --> 00:05:42,458
No matter the cost, we can’t
allow some criminal organization

75
00:05:42,541 --> 00:05:45,333
like Gui Carlin
to possess the Black Fairy Tome.

76
00:05:48,041 --> 00:05:50,541
Even if they did,
it wouldn’t make a difference.

77
00:05:50,625 --> 00:05:52,458
They couldn’t
comprehend its value.

78
00:05:52,541 --> 00:05:54,208
No.

79
00:05:54,291 --> 00:05:58,083
Still, it’s not a simple task
for us to decipher either.

80
00:05:58,166 --> 00:06:00,583
These are relics from Tupal,
the lost kingdom

81
00:06:00,666 --> 00:06:02,291
that flourished in Midend.

82
00:06:02,375 --> 00:06:05,500
All that remains of them
is the fruits of their wisdom.

83
00:06:07,375 --> 00:06:09,375
[birds tweeting]

84
00:06:12,583 --> 00:06:14,125
Hmmm.

85
00:06:21,125 --> 00:06:22,500
[door opens]

86
00:06:23,791 --> 00:06:24,916
Good morning, everyone.

87
00:06:28,458 --> 00:06:30,291
Just checking.

88
00:06:30,375 --> 00:06:32,291
Feeling any better today?

89
00:06:32,375 --> 00:06:34,333
Don’t worry about me.

90
00:06:34,416 --> 00:06:36,041
Okay.

91
00:06:37,083 --> 00:06:38,541
[sighs]

92
00:06:43,875 --> 00:06:45,958
We’ve got
the Kal-o inspection.

93
00:06:46,041 --> 00:06:48,833
Chase, you stay here
and assist the director.

94
00:06:48,916 --> 00:06:52,208
As for the rest of us,
we still have a job to do.

95
00:06:53,708 --> 00:06:54,833
Kal-o, huh?

96
00:06:57,500 --> 00:06:58,833
[MARLYA]
During the war,

97
00:06:58,916 --> 00:07:02,458
Suna, my hometown,
was burnt down by Ray Dawn.

98
00:07:02,541 --> 00:07:05,958
I had no place to go,
so I fled further north.

99
00:07:07,500 --> 00:07:09,416
At first, I stayed
with other refugees

100
00:07:09,500 --> 00:07:11,208
who were trying
to escape the war,

101
00:07:12,250 --> 00:07:16,750
but soon I grew afraid.
I knew who I was.

102
00:07:16,833 --> 00:07:18,666
A cursed child.

103
00:07:20,083 --> 00:07:21,750
[MARLYA]
Even as young as I was,

104
00:07:21,833 --> 00:07:24,166
I found people
who were kind to me.

105
00:07:25,458 --> 00:07:27,250
I knew it was
only a matter time

106
00:07:27,333 --> 00:07:29,208
before things would end
badly for them.

107
00:07:29,291 --> 00:07:31,291
[panting]

108
00:07:32,416 --> 00:07:34,416
♪

109
00:07:38,583 --> 00:07:41,625
[MARLYA] I went to the forest
on the outskirts of town.

110
00:07:41,708 --> 00:07:44,458
I don’t know why.
Maybe I just wanted to die.

111
00:07:45,833 --> 00:07:47,583
But I didn’t.

112
00:07:52,625 --> 00:07:55,166
A hunter named Victor
saved my life.

113
00:07:57,291 --> 00:08:00,250
He’s the one who taught
me how to live on my own.

114
00:08:02,041 --> 00:08:07,000
Eventually, he got sick.
And then, ultimately...

115
00:08:10,083 --> 00:08:12,041
Tsubal, The City of Water.

116
00:08:12,125 --> 00:08:14,583
Residence to Ray Dawn,
the duke of Kal-o.

117
00:08:16,125 --> 00:08:17,791
I came here
after hearing a story

118
00:08:17,875 --> 00:08:19,625
about a girl
who tried killing him.

119
00:08:20,708 --> 00:08:22,583
That was eight years ago.

120
00:08:22,666 --> 00:08:26,375
I ended up living here
until I was sixteen.

121
00:08:26,458 --> 00:08:28,083
My second home.

122
00:08:31,041 --> 00:08:32,458
[KLARA]
The city’s beautiful.

123
00:08:32,541 --> 00:08:34,833
How can this place
not brighten your mood?

124
00:08:34,916 --> 00:08:36,250
I mean, just look at it.

125
00:08:36,333 --> 00:08:37,833
[FREE]
We’re not here as tourists.

126
00:08:37,916 --> 00:08:40,666
-[KLARA] Apologies, sir.
-[SERGE] I know, I know.

127
00:08:40,750 --> 00:08:43,625
[seagulls cawing]

128
00:08:43,708 --> 00:08:47,541
[RAY DAWN]
Dorothea. Thank you for coming.

129
00:08:47,625 --> 00:08:49,041
Duke Kal-o.

130
00:08:50,458 --> 00:08:52,875
♪

131
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:56,500
[MARLYA]
Ray Dawn.

132
00:08:56,583 --> 00:08:58,125
[RAY DAWN]
Hmm.

133
00:09:04,250 --> 00:09:05,708
Ever since I settled here

134
00:09:05,791 --> 00:09:07,833
and attained the title
Duke of Kal-o,

135
00:09:07,916 --> 00:09:11,291
I can assure you I never once
laid a hand on the Fairy Weapon.

136
00:09:13,583 --> 00:09:15,916
Regardless, I must examine it.

137
00:09:17,250 --> 00:09:19,958
[FREE] Our mission this time is
to enter Duke Kal-o’s premises

138
00:09:20,041 --> 00:09:22,500
and examine the Fairy Weapon
and artificial fairies

139
00:09:22,583 --> 00:09:26,541
he owns to determine if they all
meet the legal requirements.

140
00:09:26,625 --> 00:09:28,583
It’s evident
that you harbor some ill will

141
00:09:28,666 --> 00:09:29,875
toward me, young lady.

142
00:09:29,958 --> 00:09:31,375
[BOTH inhale sharply]

143
00:09:32,416 --> 00:09:34,416
And what would
make you think that?

144
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:36,291
Experience.

145
00:09:36,375 --> 00:09:39,125
I have grown quite familiar
with your expression.

146
00:09:40,125 --> 00:09:42,208
I’ve been a called
a traitor before.

147
00:09:42,291 --> 00:09:44,583
By more than just
a few people...

148
00:09:47,500 --> 00:09:50,000
in the ten years
since unification.

149
00:09:53,958 --> 00:09:56,000
Honestly, tastes better
than it looks.

150
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:59,875
-Excuse me.
-[FREE] Hmm?

151
00:09:59,958 --> 00:10:02,958
There’s a place nearby
I’d like to visit.

152
00:10:03,958 --> 00:10:07,541
-Or rather, someone.
-[FREE] Is that so?

153
00:10:07,625 --> 00:10:10,708
I guess it’s impossible.
We’re on the job.

154
00:10:10,791 --> 00:10:13,083
[FREE]
Um, there’s an extra day

155
00:10:13,166 --> 00:10:14,916
built into
the inspection schedule.

156
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:16,583
If nothing turns up,
you’ll have time.

157
00:10:16,666 --> 00:10:19,166
And you’ll give me
permission to visit?

158
00:10:19,250 --> 00:10:21,041
-Sure.
-[KLARA] Would you mind

159
00:10:21,125 --> 00:10:23,041
if I went with you?

160
00:10:23,125 --> 00:10:26,291
I’ll be just fine.
Really. I need to go alone.

161
00:10:26,375 --> 00:10:30,208
How rude of me.
Right. Sorry for imposing.

162
00:10:31,291 --> 00:10:32,750
As long as you’re sure.

163
00:10:36,125 --> 00:10:38,333
You gotta admit, it’s good.

164
00:10:47,333 --> 00:10:51,750
Still here. Why is that?
Why am I alive?

165
00:11:06,541 --> 00:11:08,750
Don! Don Jingle!

166
00:11:10,416 --> 00:11:13,458
Hmm? What’s the emergency?

167
00:11:14,750 --> 00:11:19,583
-Marlya’s here.
-Huh? She’s what?

168
00:11:23,083 --> 00:11:25,583
I don’t believe this!
It really is you!

169
00:11:25,666 --> 00:11:28,000
This is an unexpected surprise!

170
00:11:28,083 --> 00:11:31,416
I know it’s late.
Mr. Jingle?

171
00:11:31,500 --> 00:11:33,875
What’s with all this
“Mr. Jingle” nonsense?

172
00:11:33,958 --> 00:11:36,916
Just call me “Grandpa”
like you did in the old days!

173
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:39,166
I, um,
I don’t think I can do that.

174
00:11:39,250 --> 00:11:41,833
It feels like forever
since I saw you last.

175
00:11:41,916 --> 00:11:43,625
But you’ve come
back home, finally!

176
00:11:43,708 --> 00:11:45,500
[JINGLE laughing]

177
00:11:45,583 --> 00:11:49,416
It’s been too long. Forgive me.
I’m glad you’re well.

178
00:11:50,416 --> 00:11:52,291
[SERGE]
She went in there?

179
00:11:52,375 --> 00:11:54,625
That’s where
the Biaklay crime boss lives.

180
00:11:54,708 --> 00:11:57,041
-What’s the deal?
-It could be worse.

181
00:11:57,125 --> 00:11:59,666
At least it isn’t
Gui Carlin or Arcame.

182
00:11:59,750 --> 00:12:01,875
I mean, they’re still the mafia,

183
00:12:01,958 --> 00:12:03,583
but the Biaklay motto
is basically,

184
00:12:03,666 --> 00:12:04,833
“We don’t break the law.”

185
00:12:04,916 --> 00:12:07,250
[SERGE]
I wonder how she knows him.

186
00:12:07,333 --> 00:12:08,541
[KLARA]
Good question.

187
00:12:17,125 --> 00:12:18,875
[FREE sighs]

188
00:12:18,958 --> 00:12:20,750
Can I get you
anything else sir?

189
00:12:20,833 --> 00:12:22,166
[FREE] I’m good.
Thanks.

190
00:12:30,916 --> 00:12:34,166
I see. There was a rumor
traveling around the underworld

191
00:12:34,250 --> 00:12:36,416
that you’d started
working for Dorothea.

192
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:37,958
[MARLYA]
I’m sorry.

193
00:12:38,041 --> 00:12:40,750
A lot has happened,
and I couldn’t get in touch.

194
00:12:40,833 --> 00:12:43,250
Did you at least find Veronica?

195
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:46,750
But she told me to forget her.

196
00:12:46,833 --> 00:12:48,416
To leave her alone.

197
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:50,958
Hmm. Even so.

198
00:12:51,041 --> 00:12:52,750
To think you were
once my bodyguard,

199
00:12:52,833 --> 00:12:54,916
and now you work
for Unified Zesskia.

200
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:56,958
-It’s quite a story.
-[MARLYA] I was,

201
00:12:57,041 --> 00:12:58,958
but the entire
time I was employed here,

202
00:12:59,041 --> 00:13:00,833
I never once had
to protect you.

203
00:13:00,916 --> 00:13:03,208
Well, that’s not the way
I remember it.

204
00:13:04,583 --> 00:13:07,333
I had absolutely
no qualifications.

205
00:13:07,416 --> 00:13:10,208
You gave me the job anyway,
but I knew what it was.

206
00:13:10,291 --> 00:13:13,541
A favor.
You were taking pity on me.

207
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:23,375
[metal scraping]

208
00:13:33,041 --> 00:13:36,000
♪

209
00:13:37,041 --> 00:13:38,458
[NEIN]
So, it turns out Wolfran Row

210
00:13:38,541 --> 00:13:41,583
was Ted’s point of contact
within Arcame.

211
00:13:41,666 --> 00:13:44,541
Their communication channels
aren’t usually that direct.

212
00:13:44,625 --> 00:13:47,625
That’s not everything.
The model interrupt device?

213
00:13:47,708 --> 00:13:49,458
Arcame provided those too.

214
00:13:49,541 --> 00:13:51,458
Along with blueprints
to older models.

215
00:13:51,541 --> 00:13:55,041
-So what’s their end game?
-Hang on a minute.

216
00:13:55,125 --> 00:13:56,500
Weren’t they attempting
to transport

217
00:13:56,583 --> 00:13:59,083
a large number
of artificial fairies somewhere?

218
00:13:59,166 --> 00:14:01,291
Strange coincidence
it happened around the time

219
00:14:01,375 --> 00:14:03,333
Beevee Liscar made his move.

220
00:14:03,416 --> 00:14:05,041
[CHASE]
Think they’re connected?

221
00:14:05,125 --> 00:14:07,041
[NEIN]
The man has a nose for war.

222
00:14:08,083 --> 00:14:11,625
And when he catches the scent,
he’s unstoppable.

223
00:14:14,708 --> 00:14:17,666
[SPY] Looks like the thieves
that stole Fratanil.

224
00:14:17,750 --> 00:14:20,083
Could they be headed
to Rondacia?

225
00:14:20,166 --> 00:14:22,333
Better report this.

226
00:14:22,416 --> 00:14:23,791
[SPY groans]

227
00:14:23,875 --> 00:14:25,875
[SOPHIE] If the stop the curtain
from rising,

228
00:14:25,958 --> 00:14:27,625
won’t that spoil the play?

229
00:14:27,708 --> 00:14:29,333
[SPY gargling]

230
00:14:29,416 --> 00:14:32,625
That’s the price you pay
for trying to stop the colonel.

231
00:14:32,708 --> 00:14:34,416
No matter who you are.

232
00:14:37,291 --> 00:14:38,833
[SERGE yelps]

233
00:14:38,916 --> 00:14:42,208
-About time you showed up.
-What do you mean? Never mind.

234
00:14:42,291 --> 00:14:43,916
[SERGE] I thought you were
going to spend the night

235
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:46,083
drinking alone, sir.

236
00:14:46,166 --> 00:14:48,208
[FREE] Yeah.
That was the original plan.

237
00:14:49,375 --> 00:14:51,666
So, that’s who her
mafia connection is.

238
00:14:51,750 --> 00:14:53,458
Don Jingle of Biaklay.

239
00:14:53,541 --> 00:14:56,125
[SERGE] Apparently,
they employ thousands.

240
00:14:56,208 --> 00:14:58,916
Craftsmen, porters.
The list goes on.

241
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:01,208
In terms of influence
and assets,

242
00:15:01,291 --> 00:15:03,125
they’re on par
with the nobility.

243
00:15:03,208 --> 00:15:04,875
And Marlya’s still inside?

244
00:15:04,958 --> 00:15:07,166
With no intention
of leaving, I’d say.

245
00:15:07,250 --> 00:15:09,125
We’ve been watching the place
for a while now.

246
00:15:09,208 --> 00:15:11,541
-Yep.
-All right then.

247
00:15:11,625 --> 00:15:13,375
I wonder if she’ll come back

248
00:15:13,458 --> 00:15:14,708
or leave us.

249
00:15:16,833 --> 00:15:17,916
[FREE grunts]

250
00:15:19,791 --> 00:15:21,291
[SERGE/ KLARA]
Huh?

251
00:15:21,375 --> 00:15:23,041
Sir? Where are...?

252
00:15:23,125 --> 00:15:25,666
[JINGLE] Something significant
must’ve happened

253
00:15:25,750 --> 00:15:27,041
to make you return.

254
00:15:30,708 --> 00:15:34,083
It’s nothing.
Just wanted to say hello to you.

255
00:15:34,166 --> 00:15:36,583
I was in Tsubal,
and thought I’d stop by.

256
00:15:36,666 --> 00:15:39,041
[JINGLE] Marlya.
Won’t you come back?

257
00:15:39,125 --> 00:15:40,208
[MARLYA gasps]

258
00:15:40,291 --> 00:15:42,208
Look here.
I know you’re convinced

259
00:15:42,291 --> 00:15:44,541
you bring misfortune
to others around you.

260
00:15:44,625 --> 00:15:47,083
But the three years
you were with me,

261
00:15:47,166 --> 00:15:51,291
-did anything bad happen?
-Well, no. It didn’t.

262
00:15:51,375 --> 00:15:54,375
[JINGLE] People often refer
to us as the mafia.

263
00:15:54,458 --> 00:15:56,666
But I prefer to think of us
more as a family,

264
00:15:56,750 --> 00:15:58,750
even if we’re not
related by blood.

265
00:15:58,833 --> 00:16:01,250
Isn’t that important
for you to have?

266
00:16:02,541 --> 00:16:04,916
[GUARD] Who the hell’re you?
A little late to be stopping by,

267
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:06,708
-don’t you think?
-[DIKI] If you’ll excuse me.

268
00:16:08,500 --> 00:16:11,083
♪

269
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:14,666
[MARLYA]
Why’re they here?

270
00:16:19,166 --> 00:16:22,583
I apologize for the hour, sir,
but it couldn’t wait.

271
00:16:22,666 --> 00:16:24,541
Hmmm. Now,

272
00:16:24,625 --> 00:16:27,416
you said your name
is Free Underbar, yes?

273
00:16:27,500 --> 00:16:29,750
-I’m waiting.
-Right.

274
00:16:29,833 --> 00:16:32,541
Well, I...
We thought we’d stop by.

275
00:16:32,625 --> 00:16:33,875
Say hello.

276
00:16:33,958 --> 00:16:35,458
[MARLYA]
That’s exactly what I said.

277
00:16:35,541 --> 00:16:37,958
So, a formal greeting.

278
00:16:39,125 --> 00:16:41,458
And what have I done
to earn this honor?

279
00:16:41,541 --> 00:16:43,125
Sir.

280
00:16:43,208 --> 00:16:46,250
The one who convinced Marlya
to join our group, it was me.

281
00:16:46,333 --> 00:16:50,875
-I’m not sure I follow.
-I’m responsible

282
00:16:50,958 --> 00:16:52,250
for what happens to her.

283
00:16:53,458 --> 00:16:56,333
[JINGLE]
Ah. You feel accountable.

284
00:16:56,416 --> 00:16:57,458
Yes.

285
00:17:00,333 --> 00:17:04,375
That’s fine.
But just how determined are you?

286
00:17:04,458 --> 00:17:06,666
-Whoa, Gramps.
-Determined?

287
00:17:06,750 --> 00:17:10,000
Responsibility needs
determination to stand.

288
00:17:10,083 --> 00:17:12,958
Otherwise, it’ll be swept away
when the storm comes.

289
00:17:13,041 --> 00:17:14,333
Now I’m older.

290
00:17:14,416 --> 00:17:16,000
At the age
where I can judge a person

291
00:17:16,083 --> 00:17:17,791
simply by looking at them.

292
00:17:17,875 --> 00:17:19,416
And when I look at you,

293
00:17:19,500 --> 00:17:22,083
you don’t strike me
as a man with resolve.

294
00:17:22,166 --> 00:17:24,416
Please don’t do this,
Mr. Jingle.

295
00:17:24,500 --> 00:17:26,416
-Free isn’t--
-But, why shouldn’t I?

296
00:17:26,500 --> 00:17:28,458
You are like
a daughter to me.

297
00:17:28,541 --> 00:17:30,958
Well, given my age,
a granddaughter.

298
00:17:31,041 --> 00:17:32,666
And not only you.

299
00:17:32,750 --> 00:17:35,791
I think of everyone
within Biaklay as my children,

300
00:17:35,875 --> 00:17:38,208
grandchildren, or siblings.

301
00:17:38,291 --> 00:17:40,458
Now what fool would
entrust his family--

302
00:17:40,541 --> 00:17:43,291
those he treasures,
into the hands of a coward?

303
00:17:43,375 --> 00:17:47,041
Believe me,
all of them are brave.

304
00:17:47,125 --> 00:17:48,416
Trust us.

305
00:17:51,416 --> 00:17:52,833
Hear me out.

306
00:17:52,916 --> 00:17:55,416
It’s possible you’re right
and I am a coward.

307
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:58,125
But I assure you,
when it comes to her,

308
00:17:58,208 --> 00:18:00,833
I would gladly risk my own life.

309
00:18:00,916 --> 00:18:02,875
That’s what I’m worried about.

310
00:18:02,958 --> 00:18:04,583
I don’t want you to.

311
00:18:04,666 --> 00:18:07,000
There’s a word for what we are.

312
00:18:07,083 --> 00:18:10,125
Comrades.
And though we’re not a family,

313
00:18:10,208 --> 00:18:11,708
I can say with certainty

314
00:18:11,791 --> 00:18:13,875
I’d lay down my life
if it meant saving them.

315
00:18:13,958 --> 00:18:15,125
[MARLYA inhales sharply]

316
00:18:16,375 --> 00:18:21,125
[MARLYA crying]
Stop. All of you.

317
00:18:22,750 --> 00:18:25,583
I don’t want it to be my fault
that someone else dies!

318
00:18:31,541 --> 00:18:34,958
Danger is part of the job,
no matter how careful we are.

319
00:18:35,041 --> 00:18:38,458
But even if something
tragic happens,

320
00:18:38,541 --> 00:18:40,458
we can’t blame ourselves.

321
00:18:41,750 --> 00:18:44,291
We’re willing to give
our lives to save each other.

322
00:18:45,791 --> 00:18:49,166
It’s what sets us apart
and what makes us comrades.

323
00:18:49,250 --> 00:18:51,791
It’s true. I’d do the same.

324
00:18:51,875 --> 00:18:55,208
If it meant saving
either Klara or Marlya, sure.

325
00:18:55,291 --> 00:18:56,875
And while we should
do everything we can

326
00:18:56,958 --> 00:18:58,958
to avoid those situations,

327
00:18:59,041 --> 00:19:01,125
Serge is right. I would, too.

328
00:19:02,250 --> 00:19:05,166
It’s just... I can’t.

329
00:19:06,416 --> 00:19:10,625
I know what would happen.
Every time. I’d need protecting.

330
00:19:11,958 --> 00:19:14,375
♪

331
00:19:20,291 --> 00:19:22,791
Marlya. Stop running.

332
00:19:22,875 --> 00:19:23,875
[gasps]

333
00:19:24,958 --> 00:19:27,916
Think back.
Why’d you join Dorothea?

334
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:30,250
Don’t leave before
you’ve accomplished your goal.

335
00:19:30,333 --> 00:19:34,333
I don’t know what else to say
except stay with us.

336
00:19:35,375 --> 00:19:38,791
Keep watch over us, because
we’ll always have your back.

337
00:19:54,583 --> 00:19:57,625
[DIKI] Somehow Marlya is able
to use a fairy.

338
00:19:57,708 --> 00:19:59,833
Though how it happened
remains unclear.

339
00:19:59,916 --> 00:20:02,708
You can’t simply walk away
from Dorothea once you join,

340
00:20:02,791 --> 00:20:04,125
even if you wanted to.

341
00:20:04,208 --> 00:20:06,500
[DIKI]
There are ways to go about it.

342
00:20:06,583 --> 00:20:09,458
[JINGLE] True, but her wishes
are what matter most.

343
00:20:10,791 --> 00:20:13,166
Looks like that wildcat
finally did it.

344
00:20:13,250 --> 00:20:15,250
Marlya has found some comrades.

345
00:20:15,333 --> 00:20:17,791
[DIKI]
And you trust them?

346
00:20:17,875 --> 00:20:20,291
I do.
What’re your thoughts, Diki?

347
00:20:21,583 --> 00:20:23,708
Their leader doesn’t
seem like a coward.

348
00:20:23,791 --> 00:20:25,791
[JINGLE]
He’s braver than I thought.

349
00:20:25,875 --> 00:20:27,625
My only concern is

350
00:20:27,708 --> 00:20:29,416
hopefully it doesn’t
get him killed.

351
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:31,541
♪

352
00:20:31,625 --> 00:20:32,750
[JINGLE laughs softly]

353
00:20:47,041 --> 00:20:48,416
[sighs]

354
00:20:51,416 --> 00:20:54,250
♪

355
00:21:06,500 --> 00:21:09,250
♪

356
00:22:43,875 --> 00:22:45,875
Ray Dawn!

357
00:22:45,958 --> 00:22:47,791
I don’t think he’s here
to see us off.

358
00:22:47,875 --> 00:22:49,125
I’ll handle this.

359
00:22:53,458 --> 00:22:55,333
So, Duke Kal-o.

360
00:22:55,416 --> 00:22:58,000
-How can we help you?
-I have an urgent message

361
00:22:58,083 --> 00:22:59,833
that I wish to convey
to his Excellency,

362
00:22:59,916 --> 00:23:02,500
-the prime minister.
-The prime minster?

363
00:23:02,583 --> 00:23:04,916
The contents are
in this personal letter.

364
00:23:07,208 --> 00:23:10,583
[RAY DAWN] I want your group
to see that it gets delivered.

365
00:23:10,666 --> 00:23:12,166
Once it reaches his hands,

366
00:23:12,250 --> 00:23:15,083
I expect the appropriate
measures will be taken.

367
00:23:15,166 --> 00:23:17,291
♪

368
00:23:29,916 --> 00:23:32,541
What the... Are they trying
to instigate another war?

369
00:23:39,250 --> 00:23:40,875
[CHASE] Suddenly there’s
fighting in the streets?

370
00:23:40,958 --> 00:23:42,250
[FREE]
It’s how mercenaries do things.

371
00:23:42,333 --> 00:23:43,541
[BOHME]
Liscar!

372
00:23:43,625 --> 00:23:45,041
[NEIN] If you value your life,
surrender!

373
00:23:45,125 --> 00:23:46,666
[MARLYA]
The west gate is on fire!

374
00:23:46,750 --> 00:23:48,541
[BEEVEE]
Time to raise the curtain!

